    "description": "Module-by-module Postman collection generated from the current NestJS controllers on 2026-04-22.\n\nAuth model:\n- Protected routes read `access_token` from cookies only.\n- `POST /api/auth/login`, `POST /api/auth/refresh`, and `POST /api/auth/switch-workspace` include test scripts that capture `access_token` and `refresh_token` from `Set-Cookie` headers into collection variables.\n- `POST /api/auth/refresh` expects the `refresh_token` cookie.\n- Ops Inbox and Ops Alerts are plan-gated and require a `pro` or `enterprise` workspace.\n\nNotes:\n- File import endpoints use `form-data` with a `file` field.\n- Stripe webhook expects raw JSON plus a `stripe-signature` header.\n- SSE notifications use `text/event-stream` and keep the connection open.",
